---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import JsonLd from '~/components/common/JsonLd.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Coated vs Laminated Fabric — Which Construction Is Better?',
  description: 'Compare coated and laminated fabric constructions across performance, durability, breathability, cost, and applications. Make an informed fabric decision.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: true,
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <JsonLd
    type="Article"
    article={{
      headline: 'Coated vs Laminated Fabric — Which Construction Is Better?',
      description: 'Compare coated and laminated fabric constructions across performance, durability, breathability, cost, and applications. Make an informed fabric decision.',
      datePublished: '2026-07-06',
    }}
    data={{ url: 'https://seekingtex.com/compare/coated-vs-laminated' }}
  />
  <JsonLd type="BreadcrumbList" breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Compare', href: '/compare' }, { name: 'Coated vs Laminated' }]} />
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-24 px-6">
    <a href="/products" class="text-sm text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700">&larr; Products</a>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Coated vs Laminated Fabric</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-500">The definitive comparison between coated and laminated fabric constructions — covering everything a buyer needs to know.</p>

    <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Coated Fabric</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Construction:</strong> Liquid polymer (PU, PVC, acrylic) applied directly to fabric surface via knife coating, roller coating, or dip coating.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Cost:</strong> Lower cost than lamination. Simple manufacturing process with lower material costs.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Breathability:</strong> Limited — coating fills fabric pores, reducing air and moisture vapor transmission.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Durability:</strong> Coating can crack, peel, or dissolve with washing and flexing over time.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget outerwear, light rain protection, tents, bags, industrial fabrics, upholstery.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Laminated Fabric</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Construction:</strong> Pre-formed membrane (PU, PTFE, ePTFE) bonded to fabric using heat, pressure, and adhesive — retains fabric breathability.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Cost:</strong> Higher cost — membrane production and precision lamination require advanced equipment.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Breathability:</strong> Excellent — microporous or hydrophilic membranes allow moisture vapor transmission while blocking liquid water.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Durability:</strong> Membrane can delaminate from fabric over time, but quality laminates last 3-5+ years with care.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Best for:</strong> High-performance outerwear, ski wear, professional rainwear, tactical shells, medical protective wear.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b-2 border-gray-200">
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Factor</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-sky-700">Coated</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-emerald-700">Laminated</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ['Manufacturing', 'Low cost, simple process', 'High cost, complex process'],
              ['Waterproofness', 'Good (coating dependent)', 'Excellent (membrane dependent)'],
              ['Breathability', 'Poor to moderate', 'Good to excellent'],
              ['MVTR Range', '500-3000 g/m²/24hr', '5000-30000+ g/m²/24hr'],
              ['Weight', 'Adds significant weight', 'Minimal added weight'],
              ['Drape/Hand Feel', 'Stiffer, rubbery feel', 'Soft, fabric-like drape'],
              ['Flexibility', 'Stiffens in cold', 'Remains flexible in cold'],
              ['Wash Durability', 'Coating degrades with washing', 'Membrane lasts with proper care'],
              ['Repairability', 'Can be recoated', 'Cannot be repaired'],
              ['Environmental', 'Some coatings contain solvents', 'PUR laminates preferred'],
            ].map((row, i) => (
              <tr class={i % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-white' : 'bg-gray-50'}>
                {row.map((cell, j) => (
                  <td class={`px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-200 ${j === 0 ? 'font-medium text-gray-700' : 'text-center text-gray-600'}`}>{cell}</td>
                ))}
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-50 to-blue-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-sky-200">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">The Verdict</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">For 80% of performance outerwear applications, <strong>laminated fabric</strong> is the better choice. The combination of waterproofness, breathability, and fabric-like drape justifies the higher cost. Choose <strong>coated fabric</strong> only for budget-conscious products, applications where breathability is not critical (tents, bags, industrial covers), or when the coating adds specific functional benefits (PVC for maximum waterproofness). For professional rainwear, ski wear, and outdoor shells, lamination is the standard.</p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
        <a href="/products" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-full text-sm font-medium hover:bg-gray-800 transition">Shop Laminated Fabrics</a>
        <a href="/guides" class="px-6 py-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium hover:border-gray-400 transition">Buying Guides</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="sr-only" data-ai-block="definition" aria-hidden="true">
    <p>Definitive comparison between coated and laminated fabric constructions. Covers manufacturing, waterproofness, breathability, weight, drape, flexibility, wash durability, repairability, and environmental factors. Coated fabrics offer lower cost and simple manufacturing but limited breathability and coating degradation. Laminated fabrics offer excellent waterproofness and breathability, soft drape, and long-lasting performance but at higher cost. Recommendation: laminated for performance outerwear, coated for budget/industrial applications where breathability is not critical.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
